====Definitions====
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# to [[swallow]] {{gl|to cause food, drink, etc. to pass from the mouth into the stomach}}
#: {{zh-x|囫圇吞棗|{{lit|to '''swallow''' a jujube whole}} > figuratively, "to accept without thinking; to read without understanding"}}
#* {{zh-x|子-胥 出走，邊-候 得 之。子-胥 曰：「上 索 我 者，以 我 有 美-珠 也。今 我 已 亡 之 矣。我 且 曰 子 取 吞 之。」候 因 釋 之。|When Tzŭ-hsü was making his escape, a frontier patrol caught him. Tzŭ-hsü said: "The authorities want me because they think I have a beautiful pearl. Now I have already lost it. But I will say that you have seized and '''swallowed''' it." Thereupon the patrol released him.|ref=Hanfeizi}}
#* {{zh-x|一 蛇 吞 象 ，厥 大 何如？|The snake that can '''swallow''' elephants — How big must it be?|ref=Chuci}}
#* {{zh-x|吞-舟 之 魚，碭 而 失水，則 蟻 能 苦 之。|If a fish that can '''swallow''' a boat be left dry by the flowing away of the water, then (even) the ants can trouble it.|ref=Zhuangzi-L}}
# to [[annex]] {{gl|territory, a country, etc.}}
#* {{zh-x|楚 欲 吞 ^宋 ^鄭 而 畏 ^齊。|Chu wanted to '''swallow / annex''' Song and Cheng yet feared Qi.|ref=Guanzi}}
#* {{zh-x|^今 ^秦 者，虎狼 之 國 也，兼 有 吞 ^周 之 意；……| Now Qin, a state of tigers and wolves, is united around the idea of '''swallowing / annexing''' Zhou; [...]|ref=Zhanguoce}}

=====Usage notes=====
In Standard Mandarin, {{l-self|zh|吞}} means "to swallow in whole or without chewing", while {{zh-l|嚥}} means "to swallow" in general. In many other varieties of Chinese however, {{l-self|zh|吞}} means "to swallow" in general.

